
# amend your commit

// when you add additional changes to your issue branch, add 
// them to your existing commit instead of making new commits

$[issue-branch] git log --oneline // confirm you have an initial commit

$[issue-branch] git status // confirm the files that have uncommited changes

$[issue-branch] git add -A // stage all the files with changes

$[issue-branch] git commit --amend // amend the previous commit

☝️  suggested espanso trigger: `amend:`

# commit message template

// when you amend your existing commit, use this template and
// then update it each time you run 'git commit --amend'

